    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "log transformation makes sense. i'll try that. but i'm also seeing some really extreme outliers in the tails that are pulling the whole line towards them. how do i deal with those specific points without just deleting them manually?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Outliers, especially those pulling the line, are a real pain in the backside, and you've hit on a common problem. You can't just toss them; a good, robust approach is to use **robust regression techniques**. Instead of standard Ordinary Least Squares (OLS), which is very sensitive to those big jumps, you can switch to methods like **RANSAC** or **M-estimation**. These methods are designed to give less weight to those extreme points, allowing the bulk of your data to define the line, much like a sturdy pile of rocks resisting a single, weak pebble.",
      "source": "target",
